Use the standard library
This is how to get_closest_vowel of word:
  Remember that vowels is ["a", "e", "i", "o", "u"]
  Remember that text is word
  When isarray of word is yes, then:
    Remember that text is ""
    Remember that i is 0
    Do this word's length times:
      Remember that text is "{text}{tostring of item i in word}"
      Increase i by 1
    End do
  End when
  Remember that n is text's length
  When n is less than 3, then:
    The answer is nothing
  End when
  Remember that i is diff of n and 2
  Do this diff of n and 2 times:
    Remember that ch is item i in text
    When ch is in vowels, then:
      Remember that left is item diff of i and 1 in text
      Remember that right is item sum of i and 1 in text
      When left is not in vowels, then:
        When right is not in vowels, then:
          The answer is ch
        End when
      End when
    End when
    Decrease i by 1
  End do
  The answer is nothing
Now you know